text: Star Channel is a Russian pay television owned by Warner Bros. Discovery EMEA. The channel launched as FX on 5 April 2008 in the Baltics and in Russia and the CIS on 10 August 2008 but was replaced by Discovery Home & Health on 6 March 2013. The channel started broadcasting in 16:9 aspect ratio on 21 September 2014. On March 9, 2022, Discovery Home & Health closed in Russia and Belarus due to the 2022 Russian invasion of Ukraine. On 29 May 2024, Warner Bros. Discovery EMEA announced that Discovery Home & Health in the Baltics and the CIS would be rebranded as Star Channel on 29 June 2024. == Logos == file:FX Latin America logo.jpg|5 April 2008-1 September 2010 file:FX International logo.svg|1 September 2010-6 March 2013 file:Discovery H&H.png;|6 March 2013-29 June 2024 file:Star Channel 2023.svg|29 June 2024-present Category:Television channels in Europe
